The paper deals with propositional theories and their logical operations, which are central to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves complexity analysis and algorithms for manipulating logical structures, which are relevant to logic and computation (cs.LO) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses counting models and belief revision, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and programming languages (cs.PL).
